20/01/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The presidency of the Democratic Union for Integration (DUI) has nominated deputy leader Agron Buxhaku as deputy chairman of the Macedonian Parliament.
Also Saturday (18 January), Hysni Shaqiri was appointed co-ordinator of DUI's parliamentary group.
DUI spokeswoman Ermira Mehmeti describes co-operation with coalition partner, the Social Democratic Alliance of Macedonia as successful, adding that DUI is content with government efforts to increase ethnic Albanian representation in public administration.
(Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 20/01/03;
MTV1, MIA - 18/01/03)
